<div id="right-col">
<h2>How it works</h2>
<p>
En email invitation will be sent to participants. Then, after logging-in with their facebook accounts, they will be assigned and alias, and immediately they will be able to provide and discuss answers under this alias. They can submit answers until the last date for answers, and after that they will be able to cast 10 votes for the best answers.
</p>

<p>
The rules of the system are:
</p>

<ul>
<li>users participate under an alias</li>

<li>users can vote only after the last date for answers, and voting is closed 3 days after</li>

<li>vote counts are shown only after voting is closed</li>

<li>votes are kept secret (no one is informed of who voted for what)</li>

<li>real identities are revealed at the end (so that the authors of the answers can be known)</li>

<li>participants can invite others to participate</li>

<li>question is open for public view, but only invited friends can participate</li>
</ul>

<p>These rules can be changed using the advanced-view questionnaire.</p>

</div>

